{"lemma": "جُنْد", "slug": "جُنْد", "root": "ج.ن.د", "root_slug": "ج-ن-د", "root_link": "/words/roots/ج-ن-د", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "جُنْد", "root": "جند", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 29}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n6459"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%92%D8%AF"}}, "translations": {"en": "soldiery", "fa": "سپاه", "ur": "فوج", "tr": "ordu", "id": "pasukan", "bn": "সেনা", "es": "ejército", "fr": "armée", "de": "Truppe", "ru": "войско", "zh": "军队"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "soldiery; armed forces", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "soldiery; armed forces; the military, the army, the troops", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a type of administrative division, sometimes translated as “military district”, notably instituted by the Umayyad Caliphate"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Borrowed from Aramaic גּוּדָא (guddā) / ܓܘܢܕܐ (gundā), from Middle Persian gwnd (gund, “army, troop”)."}, "ipa": ["/d͡ʒund/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n6459", "headword_ar": "جُنْدٌ", "root": "jnd", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "[a coll. gen. n.]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An army; a military force; a legion; a body of troops"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "soldiers;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a collected body of men prepared for war:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "auxiliaries:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, L, Msb, K:) n. un. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "junodiY~N", "text_ar": "جُنْدِىٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a trooper; a soldier; an auxiliary"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruwmiY~N", "text_ar": "رُومِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is n. un. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruwmN", "text_ar": "رُومٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) pl. of the former,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "junuwdN", "text_ar": "جُنُودٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Mgh, Msb) and [pl. of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ajonaAdN", "text_ar": "اَجْنَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Mgh, Msb.) It is said in a trad., ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^arowaAHu junuwdN mujan~adapN", "text_ar": "الاَرْوَاحُ جُنُودٌ مُجَنَّدَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, L)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Souls are troops collected together:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning that they are created of two parties, each party agreeing together, and disagreeing with the other party, like two armies opposed, each to the other. (L.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Any kind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "species, of creatures,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "created things, regarded as alone, by itself,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "apart from others."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, * TA.) It is said in a prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a lil~hi junuwdFA minohaA AlEasalu", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ لِلّهِ جُنُودًا مِنْهَا العَسَلُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily to God belong kinds,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "species, of created things"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by means of which He effects his purposes as by armies"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "auxiliaries"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of which is honey:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Z, K:) first said by Mo'áwiyeh, when he heard that El-Ashtar had been given to drink some honey containing poison, in consequence of which he died: and used on the occasion of rejoicing at a misfortune that has befallen an enemy: it occurs in the history of El-Mes'oodee thus;"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a lil~hi junodFA", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ لِلّهِ جُنْدًا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY AlEasali", "text_ar": "فِى العَسَلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (MF.) ―         -b3-  Also, [as a term used in Syria, and afterwards by the Arabs from Syria in Spain,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A city"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with its territory;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 470}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "province,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "district"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (K:) or particularly"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a city of Syria"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with its territory"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (AO, TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ajonaAdN", "text_ar": "اَجْنَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) Syria consists of five"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AjnAd", "text_ar": "اجناد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; namely, Dimashk [or Damascus], Hims [or Emessa], Kinnesreen, El-Urdunn [or the Jordan], and Filasteen or Falasteen [or Palestine]: (S, M, A:) they were thus called because the military forces were thence collected. (A.) [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mixolaAfN", "text_ar": "مِخْلَافٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["Mgh", "S", "L", "Msb", "K", "A", "Z", "AO", "TA", "M"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}